      <dc:title>Handwritten postcard from Schenker to Moriz Violin, dated April 25, 1927</dc:title>

      <dcterms:created>1927-04-25T12:00:00Z</dcterms:created>
      <dcterms:dateSubmitted>2013-07-03</dcterms:dateSubmitted>
      <dc:description>Schenker explains that what he is doing behind the scene to assist Violin in
        obtaining a post in Frankfurt, and hopes for some news from Wilhelm Altmann. Artur Schnabel
        will be more useful to his cause than Paul von Klenau and his brother-in-law Heinrich
        Simon.</dc:description>
      <dc:subject/>

    <marcrel:correspondent key="entity-000632">HSchenker</marcrel:correspondent><marcrel:recipient key="entity-000909">ViolinF</marcrel:recipient><marcrel:recipient key="entity-000913">ViolinM</marcrel:recipient><marcrel:recipient key="entity-000914">ViolinV</marcrel:recipient></sdo:itemDesc>


